  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a randomized controlled trial evaluating the effectiveness of bedside volumetric
      bladder ultrasound prior to transurethral catheterization of pediatric patients presenting to
      an emergency department with suspected urinary tract infection.

      Ultrasound prior to catheterization allows Emergency Physicians to determine if the urine
      volume of the bladder is sufficient for successful catheterization. Advance knowledge of
      insufficient urine allows the Emergency Physician to defer the procedure until success is
      likely.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
