  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Children 0-36 months of age

          -  Require urethral catheterization for urine analysis

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Recently voided and unlikely to provide sufficient urine when catheterized

          -  Documented or suspected genitourinary abnormalities precluding urethral
             catheterization

          -  Indwelling catheter or urostomy

          -  Critical illness

          -  No available legal guardian or legal guardian does not understand English well enough
             to provide informed consent

          -  Technical failure of the utlrasound equipment
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
